  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">A laboratory measurement of the α -decay half-life of 190 Pt has been performed using a low background Frisch grid ionisation chamber. A total amount of 216.60(17) mg of natural platinum has been measured for 75.9 days. The resulting half-life is <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>4.97</mn><mo>±</mo><mn>0.16</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>11</mn></mrow></msup><mtext> years</mtext></math> , with a total uncertainty of 3.2%. This number is in good agreement with the half-life obtained using the geological comparison method.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
